{
  "page": "Miller's sons",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"min-width:22em;max-width:32em;border-collapse:separate;border-spacing:3px\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;font-size:125%;font-weight:bold;font-weight:bold; background: none; line-height: 1.1em;\">Miller's sons</th></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" class=\"infobox-image\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<a href=\"/index.php/File:The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"The heads waited by theghostofpyke.png\" src=\"/images/thumb/3/3b/The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png/350px-The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png\" width=\"350\" height=\"350\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/3/3b/The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png/525px-The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/3/3b/The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png/700px-The_heads_waited_by_theghostofpyke.png 2x\" /></a><div><a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> and the heads of the miller's sons, by theghostofpyke©</div></td></tr><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center\">\n<hr /></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Born</th><td>\nthe <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">North</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Died</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/299_AC\" title=\"299 AC\">299&#160;AC</a><br /><a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Father</th><td>\nMiller of <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Mother</th><td>\n<a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water\" title=\"Miller&#39;s wife from Acorn Water\">Miller's wife</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Books</th><td>\n<div class=\"plainlist\"><ul><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i> (mentioned)</li><li><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Dance_with_Dragons\" title=\"A Dance with Dragons\">A Dance with Dragons</a></i> (mentioned)</li></ul></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The <b>miller's sons</b> are two boys from <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a> near <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> in the <a href=\"/index.php/North\" title=\"North\">North</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Appearance\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Appearance</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Recent_Events\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Recent Events</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#A_Clash_of_Kings\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Quotes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Quotes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Theories\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Theories</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Appearance\">Appearance</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Appearance\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The two boys are of an age with <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon Stark</a>, and are reportedly similar in size and coloring,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> which may mean they have auburn hair.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Recent_Events\">Recent Events</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Recent Events\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Clash_of_Kings\"><i>A Clash of Kings</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Clash of Kings\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>After Ser <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">Rodrik Cassel</a> captures \"<a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Reek</a>\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> his party stops at the mill for a while before continuing to Winterfell. The <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_wife\" title=\"Miller&#39;s wife\">miller's wife</a> sells them hay for their <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a>, and Ser Rodrik speaks with the miller's sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/index.php/Jojen_Reed\" title=\"Jojen Reed\">Jojen Reed</a> has a <a href=\"/index.php/Green_dream\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Green dream\">green dream</a> of Reek skinning off the faces of <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon Stark</a>, who laid dead at his feet. After Reek is brought to Winterfell and imprisoned in the dungeons, Jojen tells Bran about that green dream and others.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>When <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a> leads <a href=\"/index.php/Ironborn\" title=\"Ironborn\">ironborn</a> raiders to <a href=\"/index.php/Capture_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Capture of Winterfell\">capture Winterfell</a>, Bran and Rickon become his prisoners and <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostages</a>. '\"Reek\", freed from Winterfell's dungeons, swears himself to Theon.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Bran and Rickon apparently escape Winterfell with the help of <a href=\"/index.php/Osha\" title=\"Osha\">Osha</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Hodor\" title=\"Hodor\">Hodor</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Meera_Reed\" title=\"Meera Reed\">Meera</a> and Jojen Reed. Theon gathers a search party, including Reek, Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a>, and the <a href=\"/index.php/Kennelmaster\" title=\"Kennelmaster\">kennelmaster</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Farlen\" title=\"Farlen\">Farlen</a> and his <a href=\"/index.php/Dog\" title=\"Dog\">dogs</a>, but fails to track them down in the <a href=\"/index.php/Wolfswood\" title=\"Wolfswood\">wolfswood</a>. However, Reek tells Theon he has a feeling that the Stark boys are hiding at the mill, and secretly presents Theon with the boys' fine clothing he had brought along in a bag. Theon sends the rest of the search party back to Winterfell, except for Reek and three ironborn, <a href=\"/index.php/Aggar\" title=\"Aggar\">Aggar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gelmarr\" title=\"Gelmarr\">Gelmarr</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Gynir\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gynir\">Gynir</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>At the mill, Reek kills the miller's two sons, and when their <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water\" title=\"Miller&#39;s wife from Acorn Water\">mother</a> begs Theon for mercy,  Gelmarr cuts her down with one blow of his axe. The dead children are decapitated and their heads <a href=\"/index.php/Flaying\" title=\"Flaying\">skinned</a> and dipped in tar by Reek, and Theon dresses their bodies in the Stark children's finery. Theon returns to Winterfell and presents the heads and headless bodies as Bran and Rickon. The people of Winterfell are shocked and horrified to see this, and Farlen attempts to attack Theon until he is beaten senseless. Maester Luwin begs to sew their heads back on and bury the bodies in the <a href=\"/index.php/Crypt_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Crypt of Winterfell\">crypt of Winterfell</a>, but Theon forbids it. Instead, he mounts their heads on the castle walls, and burns the bodies and clothing to bones and ashes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>At <a href=\"/index.php/Riverrun\" title=\"Riverrun\">Riverrun</a>, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Catelyn_Stark\" title=\"Catelyn Stark\">Catelyn Stark</a> receives word that Theon Greyjoy captured and killed her sons at the mill on the Acorn Water, and mounted their heads on the walls of Winterfell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok55.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> \n</p><p>When the three ironborn who had gone to the mill with Theon and Reek die mysteriously, Theon blames Farlen and executes him. However, it was actually \"Reek\" who, with Theon's approval, killed Aggar, Gelmarr, and Gynir, to secure the secret of the \"Stark boys'\" deaths. Afterwards, Theon has a dream of dressing the dead bodies at the mill. Theon also has a nightmare that he is being chased by <a href=\"/index.php/Direwolf\" title=\"Direwolf\">giant wolves</a> with the heads of small children, while he pleads to himself that they are dead. Theon's sister <a href=\"/index.php/Asha_Greyjoy\" title=\"Asha Greyjoy\">Asha Greyjoy</a> visits Winterfell and tells him he was a fool for killing Bran and Rickon and mounting their heads on <a href=\"/index.php/Main_gates_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Main gates of Winterfell\">the gate</a>, as he has a made an enemy of every man for a thousand leagues, and only gives him ten men as reinforcements. \"Reek\" promises Theon he can get him two hundred men from the <a href=\"/index.php/Dreadfort\" title=\"Dreadfort\">Dreadfort</a>, and Theon allows him to leave. The next morning, Theon walks along the outer walls of Winterfell and gazes at the miller's sons' heads, thinking of how easily people were fooled.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Ser Rodrik Cassel and his army return and confront Theon outside Winterfell. Theon uses Rodrik's daughter <a href=\"/index.php/Beth_Cassel\" title=\"Beth Cassel\">Beth Cassel</a> as a <a href=\"/index.php/Hostage\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hostage\">hostage</a>, displaying her to her father standing atop the walls of the castle, between the heads of the two boys, with a noose around her neck. Rodrik is anguished, but still determined to attack. However, Reek returns with <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bolton\" title=\"House Bolton\">House Bolton</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/House_Bolton_guards\" title=\"House Bolton guards\">garrison</a>, and <a href=\"/index.php/Battle_outside_the_gates_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Battle outside the gates of Winterfell\">betrays and destroys the army attempting to retake Winterfell</a>, then reveals himself to Theon as actually <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Ramsay Snow</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> son of Lord <a href=\"/index.php/Roose_Bolton\" title=\"Roose Bolton\">Roose Bolton</a>. Ramsay then betrays Theon as well, and begins the <a href=\"/index.php/Sack_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Sack of Winterfell\">sack of Winterfell</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok66.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Afterwards, Bran Stark and his companions emerge from the crypts where they had been hiding, to find Winterfell in ruins and filled with dead residents and dead ironmen. They find a mortally-wounded Maester Luwin, who tells them that he knew the bodies could not have been theirs, as the older boy's leg muscles were not withered like Bran's paralyzed ones.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"A_Dance_with_Dragons\"><i>A Dance with Dragons</i></span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: A Dance with Dragons\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Theon, who has been <a href=\"/index.php/Torture\" title=\"Torture\">tortured</a> at the Dreadfort by Ramsay for months, finds it difficult to recall the truth of what happened to Bran and Rickon, remembering that they dipped their heads in tar.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd32.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>Having returned to Winterfell for <a href=\"/index.php/Wedding_of_Ramsay_Bolton_and_Arya_Stark\" title=\"Wedding of Ramsay Bolton and Arya Stark\">Ramsay Bolton's wedding</a>, a regretful Theon feels that the castle is full of <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghosts</a> for him.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd37.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd41.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> He thinks of the old ghosts from the <a href=\"/index.php/Crypt_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Crypt of Winterfell\">crypts</a> and the younger ones that he had made himself, including the miller's wife from Acorn Water and her two young sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In the <a href=\"/index.php/Godswood_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Godswood of Winterfell\">godswood of Winterfell</a>, Theon sees Bran's face in the <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood\" title=\"Weirwood\">weirwood</a> and momentarily thinks he is being haunted by his ghost, before recalling that they had not actually killed Bran and Rickon, but instead only miller's sons. He speaks aloud that he had to have two heads or he would have been mocked, and is overheard by <a href=\"/index.php/Holly\" title=\"Holly\">Holly</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rowan\" title=\"Rowan\">Rowan</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> Rowan accuses Theon of being a <a href=\"/index.php/Kinslayer\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Kinslayer\">kinslayer</a>, and Theon denies any relationship to Bran and Rickon while thinking to himself that the two children he killed were just some miller's sons.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd51.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Quotes\">Quotes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Quotes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>\"Reek\"</b>: You know that old mill, sitting lonely on the <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a>? We stopped there when I was being dragged to <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">Winterfell</a> a captive. The <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_wife_from_Acorn_Water\" title=\"Miller&#39;s wife from Acorn Water\">miller’s wife</a> sold us hay for our <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> while <a href=\"/index.php/Rodrik_Cassel\" title=\"Rodrik Cassel\">that old knight</a> clucked over her brats. Might be the <a href=\"/index.php/Stark\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Stark\">Starks</a> are hiding there.<br />\n</p><p><b>Theon</b>: Why there? There are a dozen villages and <a href=\"/index.php/Holdfast\" title=\"Holdfast\">holdfasts</a> just as close.<br />\n</p>\n<b>\"Reek\"</b>: Why? Now that’s past knowing. But they’re there, I have a feeling.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok50.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;\"<a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Reek</a>\" and <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>When he glanced back over his shoulder he saw them coming, <a href=\"/index.php/Direwolf\" title=\"Direwolf\">great wolves</a> the size of <a href=\"/index.php/Horse\" title=\"Horse\">horses</a> with the heads of small children. <i>Oh, mercy, mercy.</i> Blood dripped from their mouths black as pitch, burning holes in the snow where it fell. Every stride brought them closer. Theon tried to run faster, but his legs would not obey. The trees all had faces, and they were laughing at him, laughing, and the howl came again. He could smell the hot breath of the beasts behind him, a stink of brimstone and corruption. <i>They're dead, dead, I saw them killed</i>, he tried to shout, <i>I saw their heads dipped in tar</i>, but when he opened his mouth only a moan emerged...<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;dream of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>Last night he had dreamed himself back in the mill again, on his knees dressing the dead. Their limbs were already stiffening, so they seemed to resist sullenly as he fumbled at them with half-frozen fingers, tugging up breeches and knotting laces, yanking fur-trimmed boots over hard unbending feet, buckling a studded leather belt around a waist no bigger than the span of his hands. “This was never what I wanted,” he told them as he worked. “They gave me no choice.” The corpses made no answer, but only grew colder and heavier.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;dream of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><i>How did I come to this?</i> he remembered thinking as he stood over the fly-speckled bodies.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>On their <a href=\"/index.php/Iron\" title=\"Iron\">iron</a> spikes atop the gatehouse, the heads waited. Theon gazed at them silently while the wind tugged on his cloak with small <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghostly</a> hands. The miller's boys had been of an age with <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon</a>, alike in size and coloring, and once <a href=\"/index.php/Ramsay_Snow\" title=\"Ramsay Snow\">Reek</a> had <a href=\"/index.php/Flaying\" title=\"Flaying\">flayed</a> the skin from their faces and dipped their heads in tar, it was easy to see familiar features in those misshapen lumps of rotting flesh. <i>People were such fools. If we'd said they were rams' heads, they would have seen horns.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p><b>Luwin</b>: <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a>. And <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon</a> too. The <a href=\"/index.php/Gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gods\">gods</a> are good. I knew...<br />\n</p><p><b>Bran</b>: Knew?<br />\n</p>\n<b>Luwin</b>: The legs, I could tell... the clothes fit, but the muscles in his legs... poor lad...<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok69.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><p class=\"mw-empty-elt\"></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Luwin\" title=\"Luwin\">Luwin</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran Stark</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>He was <a href=\"/index.php/Winterfell\" title=\"Winterfell\">trapped here</a>, with the <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghosts</a>. The old ghosts from <a href=\"/index.php/Crypt_of_Winterfell\" title=\"Crypt of Winterfell\">the crypts</a> and the younger ones that he had made himself, <a href=\"/index.php/Mikken\" title=\"Mikken\">Mikken</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Farlen\" title=\"Farlen\">Farlen</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gynir_Rednose\" title=\"Gynir Rednose\">Gynir Rednose</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Aggar\" title=\"Aggar\">Aggar</a>, <a href=\"/index.php/Gelmarr_the_Grim\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gelmarr the Grim\">Gelmarr the Grim</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Miller%27s_wife\" title=\"Miller&#39;s wife\">miller's wife</a> from <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a> and her two young sons, and all the rest. <i>My work. My ghosts. They are all here, and they are angry.</i><sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>And for one strange moment it seemed as if it were <a href=\"/index.php/Bran_Stark\" title=\"Bran Stark\">Bran</a>'s face carved into the pale trunk of the <a href=\"/index.php/Weirwood\" title=\"Weirwood\">weirwood</a>, staring down at him with eyes red and wise and sad. <i>Bran's <a href=\"/index.php/Ghosts\" title=\"Ghosts\">ghost</a></i>, he thought, but that was madness. Why should Bran want to haunt him? He had been fond of the boy, had never done him any harm. <i>It was not Bran we killed. It was not <a href=\"/index.php/Rickon_Stark\" title=\"Rickon Stark\">Rickon</a>. They were only miller's sons, from the mill by the <a href=\"/index.php/Acorn_Water\" title=\"Acorn Water\">Acorn Water</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;thoughts of <a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<blockquote class=\"templatequote\" style=\"border-left:none;\"><div class=\"templatequotetext\"><p>I had to have two heads, else they would have mocked me... laughed at me...<sup id=\"cite_ref-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_11-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Radwd46.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup></p></div><div class=\"templatequotecite\"><cite>&#8212;<a href=\"/index.php/Theon_Greyjoy\" title=\"Theon Greyjoy\">Theon Greyjoy</a></cite></div>\n</blockquote>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Theories\">Theories</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Theories\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>It has been speculated that Theon fathered the boys, or at least the youngest one, as he bedded the miller's wife several times. However, this conjecture is disputed: Theon never considers the possibility that the children are his, which may imply that he had sex with the woman after they were already born; a proof of this may be Theon remembering \"stretch marks on her belly\",<sup id=\"cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> that could have come from childbirth.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Miller%27s_sons&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-4\">1.4</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-5\">1.5</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-6\">1.6</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok56.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-7\">1.7</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings\" title=\"A Clash of Kings\">A Clash of Kings</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/A_Clash_of_Kings-Chapter_56\" title=\"A Clash of Kings-Chapter 56\">Chapter 56</a>, Theon V.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Racok35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Racok35.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2